<subSubSection id="C3246572FF93C93CFF62FE19FA13FE6E" box="[199,1437,403,429]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF93C93CFF62FE19FA13FE6E" blockId="50.[151,1437,150,933]" box="[199,1437,403,429]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF93C93CFF62FE19FEC0FE6E" bold="true" box="[199,334,403,429]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the Manaós,earlier inhabitants of the region of Manaus; noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FF93C93CFF62FE3CFB52FDFE" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF93C93CFF62FE3CFB52FDFE" blockId="50.[151,1437,150,933]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF93C93CFF62FE3CFECCFE13" bold="true" box="[199,322,438,464]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF93C93CFE1FFE3DFDB7FE13" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[442,569,439,464]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manaos" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF93C93CFE1FFE3DFDB7FE13" box="[442,569,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">M. manaos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF93C93CFDE7FE3DFD39FE12" bold="true" box="[578,695,439,465]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF93C93CFDE7FE3DFD39FE12" box="[578,695,439,465]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF93C93CFC30FE3DFB9AFE12" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[917,1044,439,465]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conduri" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF93C93CFC30FE3DFB9AFE12" box="[917,1044,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">M. conduri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF93C93CFBBBFE3DFB1DFE12" bold="true" box="[1054,1171,439,465]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF93C93CFBBBFE3DFB1DFE12" box="[1054,1171,439,465]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF93C93CFB01FE3DFACDFE12" box="[1188,1347,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 138–144" captionStartId="40.[151,264,1634,1658]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,209,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-23@40.[156,1432,199,1611]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURES 138–144. Meri conduri spec. nov. 138–141 Male (MZSP 40750, holotype), left palp (138 prolateral, 139 ventral, 140 retrolateral, 141 detail of embolus); 142–144 Female (IBSP 7368) (142 epigyne, 143 vulva, 144 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn of duct system; FD—fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MAB—muscle attachment bands; MS—median septum; mr—membranous region; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RdP—retro dorsal tibial projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550299" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550299/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Figs 138–141</figureCitation>
) by the palp with tibia bearing a small triangular retrodorsal projection (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF93C93CFCD0FE51FC57FE36" box="[885,985,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 184–190" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[156,1418,344,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-46@49.[152,1434,334,1783]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 184–190. 184–186 Meri kaieteur spec. nov., female (AMNH, paratype) (184 epigyne, 185 vulva, 186 schematic course of internal duct system); 187–190 Meri manaos spec. nov., male (INPA 2453, paratype) left palp (187 prolateral, 188 ventral, 189 retrolateral, 190 detail of embolus). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; mr—membranous region; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RdP—retro dorsal projection; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SP—spermathecae; ST—subtegulum; tp—tegular protrusion. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550331/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 189</figureCitation>
). They are distinguished from the latter species by the RTA triangular and embolus lacking subdistal projection (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF93C93CFC18FE75FBD6FDDA" box="[957,1112,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 184–190" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[156,1418,344,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-46@49.[152,1434,334,1783]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 184–190. 184–186 Meri kaieteur spec. nov., female (AMNH, paratype) (184 epigyne, 185 vulva, 186 schematic course of internal duct system); 187–190 Meri manaos spec. nov., male (INPA 2453, paratype) left palp (187 prolateral, 188 ventral, 189 retrolateral, 190 detail of embolus). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; mr—membranous region; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RdP—retro dorsal projection; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SP—spermathecae; ST—subtegulum; tp—tegular protrusion. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550331/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Figs 189–190</figureCitation>
) (RTA roughly S-shaped and embolus with short laminar subdistal projection in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF93C93CFD74FDA9FCC0FDFE" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[721,846,547,573]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conduri" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF93C93CFD74FDA9FCC0FDFE" box="[721,846,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">M. conduri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF93C93CFCF0FDA9FC49FDFE" bold="true" box="[853,967,547,573]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF93C93CFCF0FDA9FC49FDFE" box="[853,967,547,573]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). Females are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FF93C93CFF62FDCCFA98FC42" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF93C93CFF62FDCCFC25FCFA" blockId="50.[151,1437,150,933]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF93C93CFF62FDCCFD35FDA3" bold="true" box="[199,699,582,609]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
Description. Male (IBSP 6640, 
<typeStatus id="5485885BFF93C93CFD98FDCCFD20FDA3" box="[573,686,582,608]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">paratype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length 11.8. Prosoma 5.6 long, 5.4 wide. Opisthosoma 5.9 long, 3.2 wide. Eyes: diameters: 0.41, 0.30, 0.25, 0.32; interdistances: 0.30, 0.12, 0.50, 0.48, 0.35, 0.20. Legs: I: 32.7 (8.9, 3.0, 9.0, 9.5, 2.3); II: 35.1 (9.6, 3.2, 9.8, 10.0, 2.5); III: 23.4 (7.0, 2.4, 6.0, 6.2, 1.8); IV: 27.4 (8.0, 2.5, 7.0, 7.8, 2.1). Spination follows the generic pattern except tibia III: d1-0-1; patella IV: p1, r1; femur IV: r0-1-1. Palp: PTA anvil-shaped, as long as its widest part (prolateral view); cymbium with small retroproximal projection; subtegulum barely visible between 9–9:30 o’clock in ventral view; conductor widest at base, distally fanned; embolus subdistally curved, with large membranous region (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF93C93CFD2AFC95FCA3FCFA" box="[655,813,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 184–190" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[156,1418,344,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-46@49.[152,1434,334,1783]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 184–190. 184–186 Meri kaieteur spec. nov., female (AMNH, paratype) (184 epigyne, 185 vulva, 186 schematic course of internal duct system); 187–190 Meri manaos spec. nov., male (INPA 2453, paratype) left palp (187 prolateral, 188 ventral, 189 retrolateral, 190 detail of embolus). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; mr—membranous region; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RdP—retro dorsal projection; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SP—spermathecae; ST—subtegulum; tp—tegular protrusion. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550331/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Figs 187–190</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF93C93CFC9DFC94FC10FCFA" box="[824,926,798,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 191–195" captionStartId="50.[151,264,1971,1995]" captionTargetBox="[194,1386,1103,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-374@50.[184,1403,1090,1947]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURES 191–195. 185–186 Meri kaieteur spec. nov., female (AMNH, paratype) (191 epigyne, 192 vulva); 193–195 Meri manaos spec. nov., male (INPA 2453, paratype), left palp (193 prolateral, 194 ventral, 195 retrolateral). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550334" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550334/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">193–195</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF93C93CFF62FCC9FE10FC9E" blockId="50.[151,1437,150,933]" box="[199,414,835,861]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF93C93CFF62FCC9FEA6FC9E" bold="true" box="[199,296,835,861]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Female:</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF93C93CFF62FCECFA98FC42" blockId="50.[151,1437,150,933]" box="[199,1302,870,897]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF93C93CFF62FCECFEB1FC43" bold="true" box="[199,319,870,896]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Variation.</emphasis>
Females (n = 8): total length 9.2–13.7; prosoma length 3.8–5.6; femur I length 7.6–9.4.
</paragraph>
